column2: A comprehensive map of alternative polyadenylation in African American and European American lung cancer patients
We report the application of a novel method and analysis pipeline that sequences 3â€™end -enriched RNA to comprehensively map the APA landscape in lung cancer.
The goals of this study are to identify the functional role of APA in determining transcriptomic heterogeneity in lung cancer and  population differences in APA.

Ninety-eight patients with histologically confirmed non-small cell lung cancer were selected from the National Cancer Institute-Maryland (NCI-MD) lung cancer study. The study includes 98 human tumor tissues and 98 adjacent non-involved tissues (n=196 total).
Expression profiling by high throughput sequencing
